{"questionId":"13375","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Iqbal attempts three practice papers in mathematics. The probability that he passes the first&nbsp;paper is 0.6. Whenever he gains a pass in a paper, his confidence increases so that the&nbsp;probability of him passing the next paper increases by 0.1. Whenever he fails a paper the&nbsp;probability of him passing the next paper is 0.6.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the probability that Iqbal passes at least two of the papers he attempts.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>probability (at least twice)&nbsp;=</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {0.6 \\times 0.7 \\times 0.8} \\right) + \\left( {0.6 \\times 0.7 \\times 0.2} \\right) + \\left( {0.6 \\times 0.3 \\times 0.6} \\right) + \\left( {0.4 \\times 0.6 \\times 0.7} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.7</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.8</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.7</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.3</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.4</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.7</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {0.6 \\times 0.7} \\right) + \\left( {0.6 \\times 0.3 \\times 0.6} \\right) + \\left( {0.4 \\times 0.6 \\times 0.7} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.7</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.3</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.4</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.7</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award<em><strong> M1</strong></em> for summing all required probabilities.</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>= 0.696<em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13375","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_3b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the probability that Iqbal passes at least two of the papers he attempts.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}